List of UK academic institutions in file UK-academic-institutions.csv was extracted on
2020-02-18 from http://learning-provider.data.ac.uk/, which in turn was compiled from UK Register of Learning Providers
https://www.ukrlp.co.uk/. It contains info on UK learning providers such as their official/normalised names,
geo location (longitude, latitude) of each institution and their web domains.

HESA_UK-higher_education_providers.csv was copied on 2020-02-18 from https://www.hesa.ac.uk/support/providers. It contains
list of official UK higher education providers together with UK region they fall into.

HESA_UK-research-income.xlsx was downloaded from HESA https://www.hesa.ac.uk/data-and-analysis/finances/table-5
and contains self-reported data by institutions on their research
income from research councils as well as other sources (e.g. industry).

HESA_UK-research-income-from-research-councils-2017_2018.csv was extracted from HESA_UK-research-income.xlsx to contain
only data about research council grants.

HESA_UK-research-income-other-sources-2017_2018.csv was extracted from HESA_UK-research-income.xlsx to contain
only data about research grants from sources other than research councils.

HESA_UK-research-income_combined.csv is a table merged from the previous two.

R_and_D_expenditure_per_region.xls was downloaded from the Office fo National Statistics
https://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/governmentpublicsectorandtaxes/researchanddevelopmentexpenditure/datasets/ukgrossdomesticexpenditureonresearchanddevelopmentregionaltables
and provides annual estimates of research and development by UK country and region by business enterprise,
higher education, government, research councils and private non-profit organisations.

R_and_D_expenditure_per_region_2017.csv is the processed version of R_and_D_expenditure_per_region.xls containing a
summary table.